  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers may read both base text and ruby text, or provide options for users to hear annotations</li>
      <li>The <code>&lt;rp&gt;</code> fallback ensures annotations appear in parentheses when ruby is not supported</li>
      <li>Ruby text benefits language learners and those with reading difficulties</li>
      <li>The <code>data-ruby="hide"</code> mode keeps annotations in the DOM for accessibility even when visually hidden</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

